thork@ifi.uio.no (Thor Oddleif Kristoffersen) writes:

> 
> In article <CpGJr7.Kw@freenet.carleton.ca>, ab606@FreeNet.Carleton.CA (Ted Re
> >I am in the process of writing a one time message pad implementation.
> > [...]
> >Some of the capabilities I hope to incorporate will be:
> > 
> >	a.  A selection of random number generators;
> >	b.  User defined random number generators;
> 
> I hope you're not planning on using pseudo random number
> generators. A One Time Pad must not only be "one time", but
> the numbers have to be truly random and independent. In
> practice this means that the numbers must be generated by
> some quantum mechanical process like radioactive decay,
> semiconductor junction noise, thermal noise, throwing dice
> etc.
 
Or timing the interval between sensible remarks by Sternlight...
 

